Common.Strapline.Common.Text: STAGE 1 RELEASE - FREESTANDING INDUSTRIAL BUILDING WITH HUGE CONCRETE YARD

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The property is centrally located between the Cumberland Highway & Woodville Road with Yennora train station is approximately 2km from the site.

The warehouse is approximately up to 13.2 metres high throughout allowing up to 6 pallet high storage and is fully sprinklered, via an ESFR Sprinkler system.

Access is provided via 4 on grade roller shutter doors and 2 sunken loading docks.

A small office area is available for lease of approximately 100sqm.

Separate access is provided for cars and trucks. Truck access to the property is at the rear of the warehouse which is covered by a large cantilevered awning ideal for loading/unloading in wet weather.

High power supply of up to 800 amps can be made available on request.

For further details please contact the exclusive agents - Elijah or Jason.

We are pleased to offer this rare freestanding industrial gem in the heart of the Yennora industrial precinct by way of public auction. 

The property is situated in the heart of Yennora; on the corner of Antill Street and The Promenade, just a few minutes’ walk to Yennora train station and a short drive to M4 motorway and Cumberland Highway. 

Features of the property include:
+ Freestanding building – rare in this market
+ Fully fenced and secure yard
+ Refurbished offices and amenities
+ High clearance warehouse area with great truck and forklift access
+ Security cameras installed throughout
+ Mezzanine storage
+ Plenty of off-street parking
+ Building area of 751sqm*
+ Site area of 985sqm*
+ Perfect for an owner occupier, investor or self-managed superfund 

The property is being sold by way of public auction on the 30th May 2018 at 10am sharp. 

This is a very rare opportunity to secure a freestanding industrial building of this calibre in a tightly held pocket of Western Sydney. Contact exclusive agents from CBRE today to organise an inspection and register your interest!
